One-line definition
	Build complex behavior by combining simple objects instead of inheriting from them.

Or more famously:
	"Favor composition over inheritance."

Ex: 
	Car → ElectricCar → Tesla → TeslaWithAutopilot → TeslaWithAutopilotV2
	for every new feature, we have to implement many classes (class explosion)

	Make interfaces based on behaviour it can perform and then use those in implementing concrete class.
	ex: interface Flyable, interface Walkable
		class Penguin implements Walkable
		class Parrot implements Flyable, Walkable

		now Parrot has both function to fly and walk, but penguin has only function to walk.

		if you have used, inheritance like class Bird, and inherit Penguin and Parrot from it and applied penguin.fly(), this would be worse
		as any how you have to implement function written in parent class, to your child class, even if it doesn't support

Use inheritance only if
	Clear IS-A relationship is there
	Behavior will not change
	Base class is stable

Always prefer to use composition